@milljm I'm afraid the issue still hasn't been resolved. I've set all the paths, including the prefix and specified the Boost path. However, it still throws errors. I ran the configure directly in the metaphysiclfolder(/home/hpc4123303047/projects/moose/libmesh/contrib/metaphysicl) and the config.log is here:
config.log
Could you find any clues from it?

Dear Guillaume, I have the same problem right now (ExodusII_IO_Helper: block id XXX not found in block_ids.). It makes it difficult for us to use the TimedSubdomainModifier .
You wrote there must be at least one element in each subdomain before outputting to exodus. In each timstep? Or just the first one?
The error message states the error is thrown in libmesh. According to a backtrace I did with gdb Moose is calling libmesh in line 343 of Exodus.C (method Exodus::outputElementalVariables()). Could we insert some kind of if-condition to avoid the error? What should be checked?



